---
source: crates/cli/tests/integration/cli_help_test.rs
description: |
  Parity snapshot of `newton --help` after the spec 273 surface restructure.
  Lines under "Commands:" are sorted alphabetically; cli-framework returns
  them in HashMap order, which is non-deterministic across runs.
---
Usage: newton [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  artifact    Manage workflow output files and execution artifacts
  batch       Process queued work items for a project
  checkpoint  Manage and inspect workflow execution checkpoints
  completion  Emit shell completion script
  config      Inspect resolved Newton configuration
  doctor      Run local environment diagnostic probes
  health      Print a one-line liveness status
  help        Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
  init        Initialize a Newton workspace with the default template
  resume      Continue a workflow that was interrupted or stopped
  run         Execute a workflow graph
  runs        List and replay workflow execution history
  serve       Start the Newton HTTP API server
  spec        Export the CLI command surface as JSON, YAML, or Markdown
  version     Print version information
  webhook     Run webhooks to trigger workflows from external events
  workflow    Operate on a workflow YAML file (validate/lint/preview/graph)

Options:
      --mcp-host <HOST>  MCP server bind address [default: 127.0.0.1]
      --mcp-path <PATH>  MCP HTTP path prefix [default: /mcp]
      --mcp-port <PORT>  MCP server bind port [default: 8080]
      --mcp-serve        Enable MCP server mode (Streamable HTTP)
  -V, --version          Print version
  -h, --help             Print help
